This paper deals with privacy-preserving algorithms, specifically in the context of local differential privacy (LDP) and central differential privacy (CDP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves techniques from machine learning and statistics, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also discusses algorithms and techniques for data analysis, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of its results for industrial deployments, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
